  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "&#39;Twas on that dark, that doleful night When pow&#39;rs of earth and hell arose Against the Son of God&#39;s delight, And friends betrayed Him to His foes:",
    "v2": "Before the mournful scene began, He took the bread, and blessed, and brake: What love through all His actions ran! What wondrous words of grace He spake!",
    "v3": "&quot;This is My body, broke for sin; Receive and eat the living food:&quot; Then took the cup, and blessed the wine; &quot;&#39;Tis the new cov&#39;nant in My blood.&quot;",
    "v4": "For us His flesh with nails was torn, He bore the scourge, He felt the thorn; And justice poured upon His head Its heavy vengeance in our stead.",
    "v5": "For us His vital blood was spilt, To buy the pardon of our guilt, When, for black crimes of biggest size, He gave His soul a sacrifice."
  },
